## Why This Is Asked
Tests multi-tenant isolation, streaming ETL, and observability under scale. 

## Key Concepts
- Pub/Sub isolation per-tenant; 
- Dataflow streaming autoscaling; 
- Beam schema normalization; 
- Tenant-scoped BigQuery with day partition; 
- IAM/service accounts and least privilege; 
- exactly-once semantics and dead-letter handling.

## Code Example
```java
// PTransform sketch: normalize, enrich, and write to BigQuery per-tenant
PCollection<Event> raw = p.apply("Read", PubsubIO.readStrings().fromTopic(tenantTopic));
PCollection<Event> normalized = raw.apply("Normalize", ParDo.of(new NormalizeFn()));
PCollection<Event> enriched = normalized.apply("Enrich", ParDo.of(new EnrichFn(tenantMetadata)));
enriched.apply("WriteBQ", BigQueryIO.<Event>write()
  .to("project:dataset.${tenant}.events$")
  .partitioning("DAY")
  .withSchema(Event.getSchema())
  .withWriteDisposition(WriteDisposition.WRITE_APPEND));
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you handle tenant onboarding/offboarding and schema drift? 
- How do you test tenancy isolation and cost controls in CI/CD?
